radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild pulmonary hyperinflation and mild interstitial opacities, without a focal air-space opacity; consistent with reactive airway disease, or bronchiolitis.
Normal appearance of the right kidney and ectopic left kidney; no evidence of pyelonephritis, perinephric-fluid collection, abscess, hydronephrosis, or bladder abnormality.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Radiographs of the pelvis (frontal and frog lateral views)
radiographic_examinations.findings: Widening of the left hip-joint space, inferior and lateral displacement of the proximal left femur; suggestive of joint effusion; no evidence of osteomyelitis.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: At 19 months of age, gradual resorption of the ossification center of the left femoral head. At 3 years 10 months of age, similar findings with progressive ossification along the superior margin of the proximal left femur.
